==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ðɛns/|lang=en}}
* {{audio|en-us-thence.ogg|Audio (US)|lang=en}}
*: {{rhymes|ɛns|lang=en}}

===Etymology===
From a Proto-Germanic root ''*þan-'' + adverbial genitive ending {{m|enm|-s}}). Cognate with [[Westphalian]] Low German {{l|nds|diëne}}.

===Adverb===
{{en-adv|-}}

# From [[there]], from that place or from that time.
#: ''I came '''thence'''.''
# {{lb|en|technical}} Commonly used in property descriptions by land [[surveyor]]s, or [[aviator]]s relating to [[IFR]] established flying procedures
#: ''Cross fix at 6000 feet, '''thence''' descend to 3000 feet and fly direct to MAP (missed approach point).''
# {{lb|en|literary}} Deriving from this or as a result of this.

